      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Memorial inscription of black letters set in a background of a white octagon which is set in a square. The diagonal faces of the octagon are extend with patterned mosaic to form the square. Opening formula is typical. Both names are Greek; they are forms of Ζώσιμος and Ἴμερος respectively. One of 18 mixed funerary and dedicatory inscriptions in the church's early stratum.</p>
         </div>
